reviews_data.review_text: Cute spot! We got two tropical teas- both had the perfect amount of sweetness with crushed ice and popping bobas.
The BEST boba I’ve had in Charlotte! I moved here from Atlanta and didn’t realize how hard it was to find good boba. If you want boba, this is best spot!!

The cafe is so cute and cozy, it’s a perfect place to do work or chill. The boba here tastes good but it’s a bit watery. I have been here twice and both times the milk tea wasn’t as milky, it’s a bit thin/watered down even though I opted for no ice this time to make sure I was right. I really want to try the food here though, it looks delicious, and the cafe is in a great area.

The drinks here are okay here, if they make the right. Today was the third time in a row that they made my drink wrong, but today was even worse. The woman who made my drink today had long black hair hanging freely; it wasn’t under a hairnet or tied back in anyway. Because of that, I found a strand of her hair in my drink (that they made wrong in the first place). This restaurant has no standards, don’t go here.

I come here quite often but today was a horrible experience. I ordered the iced matcha latte with boba…this drink tasted nothing like matcha just tasted like stale milk. I came back in minutes later asking if they could make me another drink but was told no that’s how the drink tastes. Like what!!! I Barely drunk any of it so I had to pay again for a different drink they wouldn’t even offer to remake it. After today they will not be getting anymore money from me.

First time, very impressed, found a fly in my boba cup. I chewed it, and took it out, eewwww, a fly 🤮
And by the way, boba was too hard. I’m a fan of boba but I don’t like their boba at all.

This is definitely my new favorite place. peaceful place to enjoy a  meal, pastry or drink. I had the Manh-Mi with lemongrass chicken and fried calamari and both were excellent! will be back for sure!

Stopped in today while I was waiting on my order from Chic O Rico. This Tea Fusion location is much larger than the location in University City in Charlotte. The atmosphere is warm and cozy. They do offer more food options than that location. I came in for a Coffee Tiger and got my kids a Strawberry Tropical Fresh Tea and my husband got a Strawberry Shortcake for dessert (he said it was okay). The service was good, she answered some questions that I had about things on the menu and was very pleasant. We were in and out so not much to rate.
So delicious! I ordered a winter melon tea w chia seeds. It was bussin, so delicious . Ill def be back

This place was a delight! We dove into a variety of dishes, including potstickers, a flavorful vermicelli bowl with lemongrass chicken, and a selection of refreshing teas. Everything was fantastic - the food arrived piping hot and fresh, and the service was attentive. There was a bit of a wait for the food, but the high quality absolutely made it worthwhile.
My favorite lychee frozen boba tea with passion fruit jellys

I've been coming to this place for the last 2 years and the place has undergone some renovations. It was always good to begin with but the renovations have taken it up a notch. The portions of both the tea's and the food are generous. You really can't go wrong with any of the flavors they offer and their fried tofu is top notch.
Fav Boba place
Travelled 6+ hours to try! Lovely decor. AMAZING FOOD! BEST BÁNH MÌ WE HAD IN WHILE! Totally recommend the avocado smoothie (very authentic!) Would definitely recommend!

Yummy coffee & desserts!

I had the chocolate chip cookie it was so good I highly recommend it.

Came back to try the banh mi and sea salt coffee it was amazing!!!!
Amazing environment and awesome food. Feels super cozy and welcoming.
Delicious Vietnamese iced coffee!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you! I’m glad that you like it

reviews_data.review_text: Great place to get boba tea
Nice dining area with artsy walls, great for background photos. Two entrances/exit and lots of parking spaces. Food and beverages are great!

I really liked the bubble tea Coconut.
And the service and environment are very good too !
Could nap here after tea and bahn mi. Thank you!
I ordered the mangonada, and it was the perfect mix of spicy and sweet! Drinks are inexpensive, and the workers are so helpful with picking the right drink! Will definitely come by again, 10/10!!
We love pop corn chicken there and mason jar fruit tea. Nice decor and good vibes.

Cute place, very clean, so many choices of bubble tea, snack and even Vietnamese dishes like banh mi, pho and bun bo hue. I had Hokkaido milk tea and takoyaki. The milk tea is not too sweet which is good and takoyaki is tasty. Highly recommend :)
We got the usual drinks like tea and coffee did not take anything out of the ordinary (. Nice service, clean and pleasant place. A variety of bakery and a different assortment of drinks.
I came here yesterday and had the BEST boba I’ve ever tasted. I would definitely recommend the grilled pork banh mi, very filling and delicious.
I had the vanilla bean boba and my hubby had the coffee boba both were delicious but the vanilla bean was the best boba tea I've ever had

reviews_data.review_text: Took my granddaughter there because she wanted to try boba...ended up loving it myself. Great atmosphere. Nice inviting tables, and a big couch and comfy chairs to sit and just hang out with your people. It was the first time I had ever had boba as well... So, I don't know what it's supposed to taste like... But it was really amazing! One thing I do not like about the place is they have a QR code you can scan to enter your office for free breakfast or something like that. Whoever is in charge of that, text way too much

Love this place! I heard it was under new management and the new folks here are super nice. I got the ham and cheese crossiants while my kids got their favorite popcorn chicken. Of course we all got our boba tea too. Everything here is fresh and we'll be making a weekly visit here.

It is hard to no longer have Queen City Tea Bar which just had phenomenal selection and always the perfect balance in flavors. The new decorations in the place are great. More modern. Staff was fine. However, as some of the other reviews have mentioned, it is way too sweet. I am sure you can ask for less sweetness, but it is striking how sweet it is. The boba itself was clearly fresh. The flavor that I had (coconut) just tasted like sugar, no identifiable taste outside of that. I hope they can consider adjusting their formulations.

Tea Fusion took over Queen City Tea Bar, and in comparison it went downhill. W e have visited 3X so far and everything is way over sweetened, the selections aren’t as great, and the price has almost DOUBLED that of QC Tea Bar! I don’t think they realize their main customer base will be Charlotte Catholic HS students who are used to paying $4-$5 for drink at QC and Kung Fu Tea. They cannot seriously think charging $7-$10 per drink will retain customers!?
The vibes here are fun and the staff was super friendly. I tried the popcorn chicken and avocado bubble tea and would definitely recommend!
Super excited when I heard that a new location was opening in Pineville! The variety of flavors was great and the banh mi was amazing! Definitely would go again!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for you review. We are working on expand our food menu. We love to see you back!

reviews_data.review_text: Bias probably as I really miss QC Tea. This menu is different of course but the quality is way lower than QC. The crushed ice gets sucked up in the Boba straw, the flavors are bland and there are very limited milk tea options, with no room for getting creative.  Been twice now and not sure I'll be back, unless they can make some changes.

Previously Queen City Tea bar.
Has many many flavors, but none that stand out as anything unique. No real variety on the actual tea, either. Everything is just one kind of green tea. Immensely disappointing.  Much of what I can find here, I can find done much better at smaller places.
But The lack of continued support of the local artists that Queen City supported is why they have lost my business.

(Staff was Very sweet, however. I appreciate them.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hi, we are now having black tea as another option, and we are working on the menu for both food and drink to make it better.
